, buckle tram tracks in Germany]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132061092.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/watch-europe-record-heatwave-melts-roads-in-france-buckle-tram-tracks-in-germany/articleshow/132061092.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/watch-europe-record-heatwave-melts-roads-in-france-buckle-tram-tracks-in-germany/articleshow/132061092.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-29T08:26:31+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132061707,imgsize-5167261.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[US, Iran agree to halt attacks after counter-strikes; Qatar to host Hormuz talks on Tuesday]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132058740.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Amidst escalating tensions, the United States and Iran have agreed to a ceasefire and will resume talks in Doha, Qatar, to de-escalate the dispute over the Strait of Hormuz. Following days of military exchanges, both nations will halt counter-strikes, allowing vessels to navigate freely. The discussions aim to resolve differing interpretations of a recent memorandum of understanding concerning maritime passage and port access.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/us-iran-agree-to-halt-attacks-after-counter-strikes-qatar-to-host-hormuz-talks-on-tuesday/articleshow/132058740.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/us-iran-agree-to-halt-attacks-after-counter-strikes-qatar-to-host-hormuz-talks-on-tuesday/articleshow/132058740.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-29T03:28:16+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132058741,imgsize-119956.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Trump ally tells migrants to seek permanent status or leave US: 'Fill out paperwork or...']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132058429.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/trump-ally-tells-migrants-to-seek-permanent-status-or-leave-us-either-fill-out-paperwork-or-well-help-you-get-back-/articleshow/132058429.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/trump-ally-tells-migrants-to-seek-permanent-status-or-leave-us-either-fill-out-paperwork-or-well-help-you-get-back-/articleshow/132058429.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-29T02:09:08+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132058502,imgsize-88694.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Pakistan carries out 'calibrated strikes' near Afghanistan border, 29 militants killed]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132058492.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/pakistan-carries-out-calibrated-strikes-near-afghanistan-border-29-militants-killed/articleshow/132058492.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/pakistan-carries-out-calibrated-strikes-near-afghanistan-border-29-militants-killed/articleshow/132058492.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-29T02:02:08+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132058496,imgsize-160142.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘A man does not die alone’: Chilling messages left by Bangladeshi man before killing family]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132056575.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A haunting social media message has surfaced in connection with a horrific triple homicide in Rome, where a father, mother, and their young daughter were discovered lifeless. The primary suspect, 43-year-old Shahadat Hossain from Bangladesh, is the focus of an extensive manhunt by the police. His ominous post, stating, 'A man does not die alone,' is now pivotal to the ongoing investigation.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/a-man-does-not-die-alone-chilling-messages-left-by-bangladeshi-man-before-killing-family-of-3-in-italy/articleshow/132056575.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/a-man-does-not-die-alone-chilling-messages-left-by-bangladeshi-man-before-killing-family-of-3-in-italy/articleshow/132056575.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-29T01:22:47+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132058424,imgsize-85956.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['No choice but to build atomic bomb': IRGC-linked media urges Iran to pursue nuclear weapon despite US deal]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132056302.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/no-choice-but-to-build-atomic-bomb-irgc-linked-media-urges-iran-to-pursue-nuclear-weapon-despite-us-deal/articleshow/132056302.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/no-choice-but-to-build-atomic-bomb-irgc-linked-media-urges-iran-to-pursue-nuclear-weapon-despite-us-deal/articleshow/132056302.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-28T23:21:17+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132056755,imgsize-111131.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Korean proverb of the day: 'When whales fight, the shrimp’s back gets broken']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132056396.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A centuries-old Korean proverb, "When whales fight, the shrimp's back gets broken," vividly illustrates how the powerless suffer during conflicts between the influential. This timeless wisdom, originating from oral tradition, remains strikingly relevant today, applying to everything from international relations and corporate disputes to family struggles. Its enduring power lies in its simple yet potent imagery, reminding us that even seemingly distant battles have far-reaching consequences for the vulnerable.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/korean-proverb-of-the-day-when-whales-fight-the-shrimps-back-gets-broken-a-brutal-reminder-that-when-giants-clash-the-smallest-in-the-room-suffer-in-silence/articleshow/132056396.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/korean-proverb-of-the-day-when-whales-fight-the-shrimps-back-gets-broken-a-brutal-reminder-that-when-giants-clash-the-smallest-in-the-room-suffer-in-silence/articleshow/132056396.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-28T23:11:44+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132056476,imgsize-305346.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Filipino proverb of the day: 'A desperate person clings even to a knife']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132056063.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[The Filipino saying, "A desperate person clings even to a knife," powerfully conveys how dire situations can lead individuals to make perilous decisions, often feeling trapped with no alternatives. This age-old wisdom, rooted in oral tradition, seeks to explain rather than condemn, revealing our innate tendency to prioritize survival in the face of adversity. Its lasting significance calls for compassion and a deeper understanding of challenging scenarios.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/filipino-proverb-of-the-day-a-desperate-person-clings-even-to-a-knife-and-the-lesson-it-offers-about-survival-hardship-and-human-nature/articleshow/132056063.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/filipino-proverb-of-the-day-a-desperate-person-clings-even-to-a-knife-and-the-lesson-it-offers-about-survival-hardship-and-human-nature/articleshow/132056063.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-28T22:51:45+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132056111,imgsize-35252.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Quote of the day by Barack Obama: "The best way to not feel hopeless is to…" - understand why action creates hope]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132055555.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/quote-of-the-day-by-barack-obama-the-best-way-to-not-feel-hopeless-is-to-understand-why-action-creates-hope/articleshow/132055555.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/quote-of-the-day-by-barack-obama-the-best-way-to-not-feel-hopeless-is-to-understand-why-action-creates-hope/articleshow/132055555.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-28T22:29:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132055559,imgsize-31544.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[California teacher marries Gaza man to give him US citizenship; attorney calls it 'foolish']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132054841.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[In a bold move, a dance instructor from California has wed a man from Gaza through a virtual ceremony, aiming to support his US citizenship aspirations and advocate for Palestinian rights. This unconventional union has raised eyebrows among immigration specialists, who caution about the risks of marriage fraud allegations. Meanwhile, she passionately encourages her students to engage in pro-Palestinian issues and activism.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/how-can-i-live-in-this-world-california-teacher-marries-gaza-man-to-give-him-us-citizenship-immigration-attorney-calls-it-foolish/articleshow/132054841.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/how-can-i-live-in-this-world-california-teacher-marries-gaza-man-to-give-him-us-citizenship-immigration-attorney-calls-it-foolish/articleshow/132054841.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-28T22:19:26+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132055381,imgsize-136380.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Elon Musk says Jeff Bezos’ ex-wife MacKenzie Scott giving $26.3 billion to charity is...]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132054098.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[In a surprising turn, tech titan Elon Musk has criticized the remarkable philanthropic contributions of MacKenzie Scott, arguing that her vast donations could have negative impacts on society. Scott, the former wife of Jeff Bezos, has pledged to donate the majority of her wealth, over $26 billion, to various charitable organizations. Musk's controversial remarks, including a now-deleted tweet that associated wealthy ex-spouses with societal decline, have ignited intense discussions online.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/elon-musk-says-jeff-bezos-ex-wife-mackenzie-scott-giving-over-26-3-billion-to-charity-is-making-the-world-a-worse-place/articleshow/132054098.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/elon-musk-says-jeff-bezos-ex-wife-mackenzie-scott-giving-over-26-3-billion-to-charity-is-making-the-world-a-worse-place/articleshow/132054098.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-28T21:18:58+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132054361,imgsize-112062.cms"/></item></channel></rss>